'''Frank Levick''' (1882<ref>''Derbyshire, England, Select Church of England Parish Registers, 1538-1910''</ref><ref>''England & Wales, Civil Registration Birth Index, 1837-1915''</ref> – 1 February 1908) was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played for [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]], mostly at [[inside left]], during the [[1907–08 in English football|1907–08]] season. He had previously played for [[Rotherham Town F.C. (1899)|Rotherham Town]] and Tinsley.
Born in [[Eckington, Derbyshire|Eckington]], Levick made his debut for Sheffield United on 21 September 1907 against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at [[Bank Street (football ground)|Bank Street]].<ref>{{cite web | title = Manchester United v Sheffield United, 21 September 1907 | website = 11v11.com| publisher=Association of Football Statisticians | accessdate = 10 December 2017| url = https://www.11v11.com/matches/manchester-united-v-sheffield-united-21-september-1907-57379/}}</ref> He broke his collar bone while playing against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] on New Year's Day 1908. While recovering from the injury, he contracted a cold which developed into pneumonia.<ref>{{cite book|last=Metcalf|first=Mark|title=Manchester United 1907-1911|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XSD8AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT26|year=2014|publisher=Amberley Publishing Limited|isbn=978-1-4456-2261-3|page=26}}</ref> He died of [[heart failure]] as a result of [[pneumonia]], on 1 February 1908 in Sheffield.<ref>{{cite news| title=Sheffield United Player's Death| newspaper=Sheffield Telegraph| date=3 February 1908| url=http://www.chrishobbs.com/sheffield2/franklevick1908.htm| via=chrishobbs.com| accessdate = 10 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| title=Frank Levick Succumbs| newspaper=Yorkshire Telegraph and Star| date=1 February 1908| url=http://www.chrishobbs.com/sheffield2/franklevick1908.htm| via=chrishobbs.com| accessdate = 10 December 2017}}</ref>
